---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Knitting — Yarn & Stitch Terms That Score Big"
  description="Knitting and yarn craft words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. STITCH (11pts), SKEIN (9pts), PURL (6pts). Knitting vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble knitting words, yarn scrabble terms, purl scrabble points, skein scrabble, stitch scrabble word, knitting vocabulary scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Knitting — Yarn & Stitch Terms That Score Big","description":"Knitting and yarn craft words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. STITCH (11pts), SKEIN (9pts), PURL (6pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-knitting"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is PURL a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! PURL scores 6 points (P=3, U=1, R=1, L=1). It's a basic knitting stitch that creates a bumpy texture. At just 4 letters it's easy to fit on tight boards, and it hooks to PURLS (7pts) and PURLED (9pts)."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is SKEIN worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"SKEIN scores 9 points (S=1, K=5, E=1, I=1, N=1). It's a length of yarn wound in a loose coil. The K tile (5pts) provides most of the scoring punch. SKEIN is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is STITCH valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. STITCH scores 11 points (S=1, T=1, I=1, T=1, C=3, H=4). It means a single loop of yarn in knitting. The C (3pts) and H (4pts) tiles together provide 7 of the 11 total points."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Knitting — Yarn & Stitch Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Knitting and yarn crafts contribute a surprising number of valid Scrabble words. From PURL to STITCH, these terms carry premium consonants like K, H, and C. If you've ever held a pair of needles, you already have an edge — these words are memorable, short, and easy to place on congested boards.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">STITCH (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SKEIN</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PURL</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CROCHET</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Knitting Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">CROCHET — 12 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">C=3, R=1, O=1, C=3, H=4, E=1, T=1 · 7 letters · Bingo candidate</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A needlework technique using a hooked needle. At 7 letters CROCHET is a bingo candidate worth 62 points total. Two C tiles (3pts each) plus H (4pts) give it 10 points from just three tiles.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧶 STITCH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · S=1, T=1, I=1, T=1, C=3, H=4 · Loop of yarn</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧵 SKEIN</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · S=1, K=5, E=1, I=1, N=1 · Yarn coil</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🪡 PURL</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">6 pts · P=3, U=1, R=1, L=1 · Reverse stitch</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧶 BOBBIN</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · B=3, O=1, B=3, B=3, I=1, N=1 · Thread holder</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Knitting Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WEFT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WARP</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">GAUGE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CABLE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">HANK</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">GARTER</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Knitting Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">PURL is a 4-letter gap filler:</span> At just 4 letters, PURL fits almost anywhere on a tight board. It hooks to PURLS, PURLED, and PURLING — giving you future plays. Great for burning the P tile (3pts).</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">SKEIN uses the K tile well:</span> The K tile (5pts) often sits on racks because few short words use it. SKEIN is 5 letters with 4 common tiles + K, making it reliable whenever K shows up in your draw.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">STITCH targets the TCH combo:</span> Having T, C, H together? STITCH uses all three premium-adjacent consonants in one 6-letter word. The CH combo (7pts) on a DLS becomes 14 points from two tiles.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Knitting words specialize in <span class="text-white font-medium">K, H, and C tiles</span> — mid-value consonants (3-5pts) that often block rack flow. SKEIN, STITCH, and CROCHET clear these efficiently while scoring 9-12 points per play.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-sewing/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Sewing</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-textiles/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Textiles</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-with-k/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words with K</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid knitting term instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
